---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Dust Media Server" description="Learn about Dust - a free and open-source media server built for book collectors and reading enthusiasts.">
  <main>
    <section class="page-header">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>About Dust</h1>
        <p>A media server built by readers, for readers</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mission">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="mission-content">
          <h2>Our Mission</h2>
          <p>
            Dust was created to solve a simple problem: managing large digital book and comic 
            collections shouldn't require complicated software or cloud services. Your library 
            should be yoursâ€”hosted on your hardware, organized your way, with complete privacy 
            and control.
          </p>
          <p>
            We believe that personal media servers should be accessible to everyone, not just 
            technical experts. That's why Dust focuses on simplicity, self-hosting, and 
            extensibility.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="open-source">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Free and Open Source</h2>
        
        <div class="foss-grid">
          <div class="foss-card">
            <div class="foss-icon">ğŸ“œ</div>
            <h3>MIT Licensed</h3>
            <p>
              Dust is released under the permissive MIT license. Use it, modify it, 
              distribute itâ€”commercially or personallyâ€”with minimal restrictions.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="foss-card">
            <div class="foss-icon">ğŸ‘¥</div>
            <h3>Community Driven</h3>
            <p>
              Dust is developed openly on GitHub with contributions from developers 
              around the world. Everyone's welcome to contribute code, documentation, or ideas.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="foss-card">
            <div class="foss-icon">ğŸ”“</div>
            <h3>No Lock-In</h3>
            <p>
              Your data stays in open formats. No proprietary databases, no vendor lock-in, 
              no subscriptions. Export your data anytime.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="foss-card">
            <div class="foss-icon">ğŸ”’</div>
            <h3>Privacy First</h3>
            <p>
              Self-hosted means your reading habits, library contents, and personal data 
              never leave your server. No tracking, no telemetry, no cloud dependencies.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="foss-card">
            <div class="foss-icon">ğŸ› ï¸</div>
            <h3>Transparent Development</h3>
            <p>
              Every line of code is open for inspection. See exactly how Dust works, 
              verify security practices, and audit the codebase yourself.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="foss-card">
            <div class="foss-icon">ğŸŒ</div>
            <h3>Built to Last</h3>
            <p>
              Open source means Dust can live forever. Even if the original developers move on, 
              the community can maintain and improve it indefinitely.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tech-stack">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Technology</h2>
        <p class="tech-intro">
          Dust is built with modern, performant technology designed for reliability and efficiency.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-details">
          <div class="tech-item">
            <h3>ğŸš€ High Performance</h3>
            <p>
              Written in Zig for exceptional performance and low memory usage. Perfect for 
              running on resource-constrained devices like Raspberry Pi or older hardware.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="tech-item">
            <h3>ğŸ’¾ SQLite Database</h3>
            <p>
              Uses embedded SQLite for zero-configuration storage. No separate database server 
              requiredâ€”everything in a single file that's easy to backup and restore.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="tech-item">
            <h3>ğŸŒ Modern Web Client</h3>
            <p>
              Official web client built with Lit and TypeScript. Fast, responsive, and works 
              on any modern browser. But feel free to build your own!
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="tech-item">
            <h3>ğŸ“¡ RESTful API</h3>
            <p>
              Clean, well-documented REST API with JWT authentication. Build mobile apps, 
              desktop clients, or integrations with other tools.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="use-cases">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Who Uses Dust?</h2>
        
        <div class="use-case-grid">
          <div class="use-case">
            <h3>ğŸ“š Book Collectors</h3>
            <p>
              Manage thousands of eBooks with automatic metadata, cover art, and organization. 
              Perfect for those with extensive digital libraries spanning multiple formats.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case">
            <h3>ğŸ  Homelab Enthusiasts</h3>
            <p>
              Add a media server to your homelab alongside other self-hosted services. 
              Integrates nicely with reverse proxies, authentication systems, and monitoring tools.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case">
            <h3>ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ‘©â€ğŸ‘§â€ğŸ‘¦ Families</h3>
            <p>
              Create separate accounts for family members with age-appropriate content filtering. 
              Track reading progress individually and share a common library.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case">
            <h3>ğŸ“– Educators & Students</h3>
            <p>
              Organize textbooks, research papers, and educational materials in one place. 
              Share access with study groups while maintaining control over your collection.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case">
            <h3>ğŸ¨ Comic Collectors</h3>
            <p>
              Manage comic collections with support for CBR/CBZ formats. Organize by publisher, 
              series, and issue number with automatic cover detection.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case">
            <h3>ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» Developers</h3>
            <p>
              Build custom clients and integrations using the comprehensive REST API. 
              Create tools that fit your exact workflow and reading preferences.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="principles">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Our Principles</h2>
        
        <div class="principles-list">
          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-number">1</div>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>Simplicity Over Complexity</h3>
              <p>
                One-command installation, minimal configuration, and sensible defaults. 
                Getting started should be measured in minutes, not hours.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-number">2</div>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>Privacy by Default</h3>
              <p>
                Self-hosted architecture means your data stays with you. No analytics, 
                no tracking, no phone-home features.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-number">3</div>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>Extensibility Through APIs</h3>
              <p>
                The official client is just one option. Build what works for you using 
                our comprehensive REST API.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-number">4</div>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>Open Development</h3>
              <p>
                Development happens in the open on GitHub. Feature requests, bug reports, 
                and contributions are always welcome.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-number">5</div>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>Performance Matters</h3>
              <p>
                Fast response times and low resource usage. Run Dust on modest hardware 
                without compromising functionality.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="get-involved">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Get Involved</h2>
        <p>Dust is built by the community, and we'd love your help.</p>

        <div class="involvement-grid">
          <div class="involvement-card">
            <h3>ğŸ’» Contribute Code</h3>
            <p>
              Found a bug? Want to add a feature? PRs are welcome! Check out our 
              contributing guide to get started.
            </p>
            <a href="https://github.com/dust-books/dust-server/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Contributing Guide
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="involvement-card">
            <h3>ğŸ“– Improve Docs</h3>
            <p>
              Help make Dust easier to use by improving documentation, writing guides, 
              or translating content.
            </p>
            <a href="https://github.com/dust-books/dust-server" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              View Docs
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="involvement-card">
            <h3>ğŸ› Report Issues</h3>
            <p>
              Found a problem? Let us know! Detailed bug reports help us improve Dust 
              for everyone.
            </p>
            <a href="https://github.com/dust-books/dust-server/issues" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Report Issue
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="involvement-card">
            <h3>ğŸ’¬ Join Discussions</h3>
            <p>
              Share ideas, ask questions, and connect with other Dust users in our 
              GitHub Discussions.
            </p>
            <a href="https://github.com/dust-books/dust-server/discussions" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Join Discussion
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-final">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to Start?</h2>
        <p>Set up your own Dust server and take control of your digital library.</p>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a href="/setup" class="btn-primary">Get Started</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/dust-books/dust-server" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .page-header {
    padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e293b 0%, #0f172a 100%);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3b82f6 0%, #8b5cf6 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .page-header p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .mission {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .mission-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .mission-content h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .mission-content p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .open-source {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: var(--color-bg-light);
  }

  .open-source h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .foss-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .foss-card {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .foss-icon {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .foss-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .foss-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .tech-stack {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .tech-stack h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .tech-intro {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .tech-details {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .tech-item {
    background: var(--color-bg-light);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .tech-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .tech-item p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .use-cases {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: var(--color-bg-light);
  }

  .use-cases h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .use-case-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .use-case {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .use-case h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .use-case p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .principles {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .principles h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .principles-list {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .principle {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .principle-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .principle-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .principle-content p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .get-involved {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: var(--color-bg-light);
  }

  .get-involved h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .get-involved > .container > p {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .involvement-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .involvement-card {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .involvement-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .involvement-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    flex: 1;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-final {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-final h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-final p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .principle {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .foss-grid, .tech-details, .use-case-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
